      "Grating cut away and replaced around tree"
    ],
    "summary": "On 21 September 2023 at 0745 hours, a loss of well control event occurred on South Pass 28 13(V) jacket. Production operators discovered an external leak on the production casing of Well 0693 #98, with a hydrocarbon sheen observed leaking into Gulf of Mexico waters. The total estimated spill volume was 65.7 gallons of oil. The well continued to leak until 30 September 2023 when pressure bled off to zero. The incident was caused by equipment failure due to inadequate preventive maintenance, corrosion, and erosion in a harsh shallow saltwater environment.",
